<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.2. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Overview</h2>
<p>
    This page documents the Sold To / Ship To resolution rules and the Collection Details logic (Return to Customer
    Address, Collection Address, Freight Type, Incoterm Determination, Return Location, Origin Bond) that R4C
    evaluates for every intake case, regardless of Service Type.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Purpose:</strong> Give Developers and QA a single, accurate reference for how Sold To/Ship To CMF and
    address records are resolved, how Return to Customer/Collection addresses and contacts are determined, and how
    Freight Type, Incoterm and Return Location are derived, so this logic is documented once instead of once per
    intake page.
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Reusable page: link here, do not copy</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            This content used to be duplicated across the Admin, Exception, Quality, Stock Rotation, Technical and
            Miscellaneous intake pages. It is now maintained in one place. Intake pages should link to this page for
            Sold To/Ship To/Address/Collection Details logic instead of repeating it: if a rule changes, it only
            needs to be updated here. Service-Type-specific content (Remedy options, CIRS Number rules, Return
            Reason Justification, Warranty Entitlement Check for Exchange, etc.) stays on each intake page.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.3. ">Sold To / Ship To CMF Resolution</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Sold To:</strong> All the 'Customer CMF' records which are related to the contact/account which have
        a related 'Customer Partner' record (with role code: AG) can be selected as valid Sold To.</li>
    <li>For selecting Sold To, we have a wild card search functionality which makes it easy to search and get the
        required CMF value instead of going through all the values in a dropdown.</li>
    <li>Based on the selected Sold To value, all other data will be fetched for other dropdowns.</li>
    <li>When Sold To is selected, all the other details are auto populated based on the selected 'Sold To' value.
        Values are auto populated based on the most recent case created using that particular 'Sold To'.</li>
    <li>All other fields in Request Header Details are dropdowns; if any dropdown contains a single value, it would
        be auto populated when the agent selects a value on a dependent dropdown for that dropdown.</li>
    <li>Sold To Address values are determined and populated from the 'Customer Physical Address' records which are
        related to the selected Sold To CMF having address type as 'AG/WE/RG'.</li>
    <li>From Agent UI, we can see the address records related to selected Sold To: Go to the Sold To 'Customer CMF
        record' &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; See the address Type as 'AG/WE/RG'.
        All the active addresses would be displayed for the user to choose from.</li>
    <li>The available sales areas for the selected Sold To are shown in the "Sales Area" (Sales Area = Sales org
        Code&ndash;Sales org Name/Distribution Code-Distribution channel name, e.g., EU02-U.K./02-Industrial Disti)
        dropdown.</li>
    <li><strong>Ship To:</strong> All the 'Customer CMF' records which are related to the selected Sold To and
        selected Sales Area which have a related 'Customer Partner' record (with role code: WE) can be selected as
        valid Ship To.</li>
    <li>These values are dependent on the selected Sold To &amp; Sales Area. Hence, when the Sold To/Sales Area is
        changed, the other fields should be refreshed/reset.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>We have wildcard search functionality present for 'Ship To' field also, which works similar to 'Sold To'
            search.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.4. ">Return to Customer Address &amp; Contact</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Return to Customer Address:</strong> Options are determined and populated from the 'Customer
        Physical Address' records which are related to the selected Sold To CMF having address type as 'Return To
        Customer'.</li>
    <li>Agent has search options from the dropdown to select Return to Customer address, can search by Name,
        Country, State &amp; Postal Code.</li>
    <li>To see the address records related to selected Sold To: Go to the Sold To 'Customer CMF record' &gt; Open
        the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; See the address Type as 'Return To Customer'. All the
        active address records would be displayed for agent to choose from.</li>
    <li><strong>Return to Customer Contact:</strong> These contact values are fetched based on the selected 'Return
        to Customer Address'.</li>
    <li>To see the contact records related to selected 'Return to Customer Address': Go to the Sold To 'Customer
        CMF record' &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; Open the selected 'Return To
        Customer' address record &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Physical Address Contacts. All the active contact
        records would be displayed for agents to choose from.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.5. ">Collection Address &amp; Contact</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Collection Address:</strong> Collection address and collection contact fields are only mandatory if
        Freight Type is selected as IMF. Collection address values are determined and fetched similar to 'Return to
        Customer Address' values.</li>
    <li>The options are determined and populated from the 'Customer Physical Address' records which are related to
        the selected Sold To CMF having address type as 'Collection'.</li>
    <li>Agent has a search option to select Collection address from the dropdown, can search by Name, Country,
        State &amp; Postal Code.</li>
    <li>The addresses are also filtered based on the Geo value of the selected Return to Customer address.</li>
    <li><strong>Collection Contact:</strong> These contacts are fetched based on the selected 'Collection Address'.</li>
    <li>To see the contact records related to selected 'Collection Address': Go to the Sold To 'Customer CMF
        record' &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; Open the selected 'Collection
        Address' record &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Physical Address Contacts. All the active contacts would be
        displayed for agent to choose from.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.6. ">Freight Type (IMF / CRF)</h2>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000008" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Matrix record prioritization applies to every matrix, not just Freight</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            Every matrix lookup in R4C (Freight Determination, Return Location, Incoterm, NPR Rule, Approval, MRB,
            Geography-to-Queue, Pending, NCNR) resolves ties the same way: when more than one matrix record matches
            the passed-in filter criteria, the record with the <strong>lowest
            <code>Sales_Issue_Rule_Prioritization_Number__c</code> value wins</strong> (records with no value sort
            last). This tie-breaking rule applies uniformly across every matrix lookup on this page and in Product
            Validation, not only Freight Determination. Worth knowing before assuming "no matching record" when
            actually a lower-priority record was silently preferred.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
    Once 'Return to Customer Address' is selected, Freight Type values are determined and populated from the
    <strong>Sales Freight Determination Matrix</strong>. Freight Determination is fetched from the matrix based on
    the following parameters, and the record from the matrix with the least priority number and matching criteria
    is fetched:
</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Service Type</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Remedy Type</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Country</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Return Reason</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Geography</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>
    The values are populated by filtering the matrix records by passing Remedy, Service Type, Return Reason, Geo and
    Country (RTC Address Country) fields to the matrix. If no record is found, we exclude Country and fetch the
    record. If still no record is found, we exclude Return Reason and fetch the record.
</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Freight Type – IMF (Intel Managed Freight):</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>If the customer selects the Freight Type as IMF, then all Collection Details fields are mandatory to
                proceed further.</li>
            <li>After selecting the Collection Address, the Collection Date field is enabled, and the date is auto
                populated.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Freight Type – CRF (Customer Routed Freight):</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>If the user selects the Freight Type as CRF, the Collection Date, Return to Customer address &amp;
                Return to Customer contact fields are mandatory to proceed further.</li>
            <li><strong>Collection Date</strong> will auto-populate to the current day/case creation day as soon as
                the user selects Freight Type as CRF, and all the succeeding days would be enabled for the customer
                to choose from, including holidays and weekends.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>For IMF, <strong>'Collection Date'</strong> would be reset if the case is edited the next day.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005" ac:name="warning" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">The "Geo Lead Time Matrix" / APAC-APJ day-count rule is not implemented</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            Several intake pages (Admin, Quality, and others) previously documented that Collection Date for IMF is
            auto-populated from a "Geo Lead Time Matrix," with a specific APAC/APJ 5-day vs. other-regions 3-day
            rule and a worked example. There is no Lead Time matrix in the system: R4C's matrix types are Required
            Field, Return Location, Freight Determination, NPR Rule, Incoterm, Approval, MRB, Geography-to-Queue,
            Pending, and NCNR, and no code anywhere references Lead Time, APAC, or APJ. This logic is defunct or
            was never implemented as documented, and has been removed from this page rather than carried forward as
            fact. Confirm with whoever owns Collection Date auto-population how it actually determines the date
            today before documenting a replacement.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.7. ">Incoterm Determination</h2>
<p>
    When Freight Type is IMF, the Incoterm value is determined by checking for the exact matching record, passing
    Remedy, Service Type, Return Reason, Geo and Country (Collection Address Country) fields to the <strong>Incoterm
    Determination Matrix</strong>. If no record is found, we exclude Country and fetch the record. If still no
    record is found, we exclude Return Reason and fetch the record.
</p>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.8. ">Return Location</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Return Location value is determined from the <strong>Sales Return Location Matrix</strong> using the
        selected Remedy, Service Type, Sold To CMF, Bonded Zone Indicator, and Country (IMF – Collection Country,
        CRF – RTC Country).</li>
    <li>If no match is found with the above combination, Sold To CMF is excluded and the Return Location value is
        fetched again.</li>
    <li>If no match is found, it's a hard stop and the agent is notified by a relevant error toast message.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.9. ">Origin Bond (Bonded Zone)</h2>
<ul>
    <li>If the selected RTC/Collection Address belongs to India/China, only then can the user see the Origin Bonded
        option in UI, and this value is selected as 'Non-Bonded' by default. Customer can select 'Bonded' according
        to the requirements.</li>
    <li>If the selected RTC/Collection Address does not belong to India/China, the Origin Bonded option is not
        visible in UI and, by default, it is considered 'Non-Bonded'.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.10. ">LAR Country Rule</h2>
<p>
    If a user wants to select a Collection Address with an LAR country (LAR Countries: Brazil, Argentina, Chile,
    Colombia, Costa Rica, Dominica, Dominican Rep, Ecuador, Mexico, Panama, Puerto Rico, El Salvador, Venezuela,
    Guatemala, Peru), then the RTC Address should be selected as a United States country address. Otherwise, an
    error message is displayed.
</p>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.11. ">Address &amp; Contact Add/Edit/Delete</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Agent has the option to add a new 'Return to Customer' or 'Collection' address and edit or delete previously
        existing addresses by selecting the 'Add, Edit and Delete Address' option from either the 'Return to
        Customer Address' or 'Collection Address' dropdowns respectively.</li>
    <li>Customer has the option to add new 'Sold To Contact' or 'Ship To Contact' contacts and edit or delete
        previously existing contacts by selecting the 'Add, Edit and Delete Contact' option from either the 'Sold To
        Contact' or 'Ship To Contact' dropdowns respectively.</li>
    <li>While creating a new contact record associated with the related address record, First Name, Email and Phone
        Number are mandatory fields.</li>
    <li>While creating a new address, C/O Name, Country, Street 1 and City are mandatory fields.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.12. ">Google Address Autocomplete API</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Whenever a user creates a new address or edits an existing address, based on the address entered at Street
        1, predictions (Top 5) from the Google Address API are displayed.</li>
    <li>Upon selection of any address from the dropdown, State, Street 2, City and Postal Code are populated.</li>
    <li>When using this functionality for the 'Collection Address' field, the user can create/edit any address, but
        if the address the user tries to save doesn't have the same Geo as the RTC address, the address is not
        saved.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.13. ">China Contact Consent Confirmation</h2>
<p>
    While a user is creating a new contact for a China country address, either Collection Address or RTC Address,
    the user should select the <strong>Consent Confirmation</strong> checkbox, otherwise the contact will not be
    saved.
</p>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.14. ">Embargo Check (GTS Screening)</h2>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note: Embargo check (GTS Screening)</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>When the agent clicks the 'Next' button or 'Save for Later', Country values from Sold To, Ship To,
                'Return to Customer' and 'Collection' addresses are sent to 'Embargo GTS Check' in SF to check if
                the selected country is on the 'Embargo list'.</li>
            <li>If a country is an embargo country, that respective address would be a hard stop and the agent would
                be notified by an error toast message with details.</li>
            <li>If all countries pass GTS screening, the agent is redirected to the next stage or case detail page
                respectively.</li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000007" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Check per Service Type</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            Some intake pages describe this as a single combined check across all five address types, while others
            describe a two-step flow (an API check followed by a separate local-database check). Confirm the exact
            behavior on the specific intake page rather than assuming it here.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.15. ">Where this is used</h2>
<p>
    Link to this page from the Request Header Details / Collection Details sections of every intake page instead of
    duplicating it. Pages that link here: Admin Intake, Exception Intake, Quality Intake, Stock Rotation Intake,
    Technical Intake, Miscellaneous Intake. Each intake page keeps its own
    Service-Type-specific content (Remedy dropdown options, Return Reason, CIRS Number rules, and any
    Service-Type-specific sub-flows) inline.
</p>
